cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR

The paper focuses on using computer vision techniques, specifically deep learning, to detect work zones in video footage from the SHRP 2 NDS dataset. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze and understand human driver behavior, which could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The integration of this information into the Roadway Information Database (RID) involves robotics and automation (cs.RO) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of data security and privacy in handling the large amount of video data, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
